    <main>

      <section id="traceability">
        <h2>Traceability</h2>
        <p>
          Each row maps a requirement to its implementation and test evidence.
          Cell colors: <span class="badge badge-blocking">blocking</span> issue present,
          <span class="badge badge-warning">warning</span> minor concern,
          <span class="badge badge-ok">ok</span> verified.
        </p>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Requirement</th>
              <th>Implemented?</th>
              <th>Tested?</th>
              <th>Evidence</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <!-- Reviewer: set class="blocking", "warning", or "ok" on each <td> as appropriate -->
            <tr>
              <td><span class="req-id">REQ-001</span></td>
              <td class="pending">TODO</td>
              <td class="pending">TODO</td>
              <td>TODO</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section id="commands-run">
        <h2>Commands run</h2>
        <pre><code>TODO</code></pre>
      </section>

      <section id="findings">
        <h2>Findings</h2>

        <div class="collapsible-section">
          <button class="collapse-btn" type="button">
            <span class="arrow">▾</span> Blocking findings
          </button>
          <div class="collapse-body">
            <p>TODO or <code>None</code>.</p>
            <!-- Add one entry per blocking finding:
            <div class="req-row err">
              <span class="req-id err">BLK-1</span>
              <span>Description of the blocking issue.</span>
            </div>
            -->
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapsible-section">
          <button class="collapse-btn" type="button">
            <span class="arrow">▾</span> Non-blocking findings
          </button>
          <div class="collapse-body">
            <p>TODO or <code>None</code>.</p>
            <!-- Add one entry per non-blocking finding:
            <div class="req-row edge">
              <span class="req-id edge">NBK-1</span>
              <span>Description of the non-blocking concern.</span>
            </div>
            -->
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="visual-verification">
        <h2>Visual verification</h2>
        <p>TODO: Fill when the spec's <code>Visual evidence</code> or <code>UI acceptance criteria</code> sections contain entries; otherwise state <code>None</code>. Compare the implemented UI against the referenced images (via the <code>ui-qa</code> skill / <code>browser-tester</code> agent when installed, manually otherwise).</p>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Criterion / image</th><th>Evidence (what was compared, how)</th><th>Result</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>UI-001 / IMG-001</td><td>TODO</td><td>pass / fail (observed difference) / not verifiable (why)</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section id="spec-drift-check">
        <h2>Spec drift check</h2>
        <p>TODO: Were files changed outside the design's <code>Files to change</code> list (or the task's <code>scope</code> globs, if the spec-drift hook is configured)? List each with its justification, or state <code>None</code> — unjustified out-of-scope changes are a blocking finding.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="high-risk-deep-review">
        <h2>High-risk and deep review</h2>
        <p>TODO: High-risk categories touched (security-sensitive, auth/authz, payments, migrations, infra, public APIs, large refactors, data-loss) — or <code>None</code>. For each: which escalation rungs ran (standard / security pass / adversarial pass / paid deep review with approval), and the outputs — security findings, performance findings, edge cases, reproduction attempts (reproduced vs theoretical), remediation plan. A high-risk change reviewed only at the standard level needs the reason recorded here (<code>reference/deep-review-policy.md</code>).</p>
      </section>

      <section id="documentation-decision">
        <h2>Documentation decision</h2>
        <p>TODO: Select one and fill the targets table — a task is not <code>done</code> while required documentation is pending.</p>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Decision</th><th>Selected</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><span class="badge badge-warning">required</span> — targets listed below; <code>documentation_status: pending</code> until the documenter reports and the re-check passes.</td><td>☐</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="badge badge-ok">not required</span> — no documentation affected; <code>documentation_status: not_required</code>.</td><td>☐</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Documentation target</th><th>Updated / justified unaffected</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>TODO (from the design's <code>Documentation targets</code> + anything found in review)</td><td>TODO</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section id="proposals">
        <h2>Proposals</h2>
        <p>Propose-only — nothing below is written anywhere without explicit developer approval of the exact text.</p>
        <p><strong>Decision-log entries proposed:</strong> TODO (significant decisions settled by this task — architecture choices, rejected alternatives, workflow rules) or <code>None</code>.</p>
        <p><strong>Failure-learning entry proposed:</strong> TODO (only after a meaningful mistake with a reusable lesson) or <code>None</code>.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="decision">
        <h2>Decision</h2>
        <p>Reviewer selects one:</p>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Option</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Selected</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="badge badge-ok">approved</span></td>
              <td>Task can move to <code>done</code> (once documentation is <code>updated</code> or <code>not_required</code> and non-blocking findings are resolved or explicitly deferred).</td>
              <td>☐</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="badge badge-warning">needs_changes</span></td>
              <td>Implementation defects; return to <code>in_progress</code>.</td>
              <td>☐</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="badge badge-blocking">spec_revision_required</span></td>
              <td>Spec is wrong or incomplete; return to <code>spec_draft</code>.</td>
              <td>☐</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="badge badge-warning">blocked</span></td>
              <td>External input needed; set status to <code>blocked</code>.</td>
              <td>☐</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section id="notes">
        <h2>Notes</h2>
